IBADAN – Oyo State governor, Seyi Makinde, has announced Sulaiman Olanrewaju as his new Chief Press Secretary (CPS) while retaining Hon. Segun Ogunwuyi as his Chief of Staff (CoS). Olanrewaju, who replaced Makinde’s former Chief Press Secretary, Taiwo Adisa, was until his new appointment the Group Business Editor of Nigerian Tribune. According to Makinde, his new CPS was absent from the event because he was unaware of his own appointment, adding that his decision to appoint Olanrewaju was borne out of due diligence privately carried out.